description: The Indian hockey team player Amit Rohidas has been suspended for a single game at the Paris Olympics. As a result, he will be absent from India's crucial semi-final encounter against Germany, scheduled for Tuesday.
title: Rohidas banned for one match, to miss semis against Germany

description: "She called me up around 1:30 am. She told me that there was a massive landslide in her area, and the area was being inundated. She asked me to send a vehicle to rescue them," Shanavas Palliyal, deputy general manager at WIMS, told TOI.
title: Wayanad woman who sent 1st SOS, then went to help others is also dead

description: National Testing Agency on Sunday rebutted claims that it had made a profit of Rs 448 crore in the last six years through conduct of exams, which sources in NTA said were “based on inadequate understanding and facts”.
title: Congress, government spar over NTA 'profit' of Rs 448 crore

description: A law requiring prior chief ministerial consent for land-related transactions between Hindus and Muslims is also in the works to halt what Sarma labelled "land jihad".
title: Will bring law to give life term for 'love jihad' & to halt 'land jihad': Himanta

description: Late Sunday, CM Mohan Yadav ordered the removal of the Sagar collector, SP, & the local SDM over collapse. He also suspended the chief municipal officer and a sub-engineer of Shahpur.
title: 9 kids killed as shaky wall near MP temple falls due to showers
India advises nationals to avoid travel to Bangladesh amid violent protests

description: ED has claimed the two bureaucrats in the then Baghel-led Congress govt were tampering with evidence to dilute the case against them.
title: Tainted babus contacted Chhattisgarh HC judge: ED to SC

description: Novak Djokovic, 37, competing in his fifth Games, beat Carlos Alcaraz 7-6 (7/3), 7-6 (7/2) in the final to add Olympic gold to his 24 Grand Slam titles. With the win, Djokovic joined Andre Agassi, Rafael Nadal, Steffi Graf and Serena Williams as the only players to win all four Grand Slam tournaments and Olympic singles gold, completing the career Golden Slam.
title: Viral Video: Tearful Djokovic hugs daughter after claiming gold

description: The Indian hockey team produced one of its most resolute performances in recent memory to enter the Olympic semifinals for a second successive edition but Lakshya Sen's zealous push for a gold turned into a hunt for bronze on a bitter-sweet Sunday for India at the Paris Games.
title: Hockey team in Olympic semis; Sen remains in hunt for bronze
'You will regret ...': UK PM Starmer's warning to far-right protesters
Meghan Markle reveals shocking battle with suicidal thoughts

description: Sri Lanka defeated India by 32 runs, taking a 1-0 series lead. Jeffrey Vandersay's superb six-wicket haul for 33 runs dismantled the Indian batting lineup, leading to India’s collapse from 97 for 1 to 208 all out. Rohit Sharma's 64 and Shubman Gill's 35 set a strong foundation, but Vandersay's spin proved too challenging, dismissing key players including Sharma and Virat Kohli. Sri Lanka’s lower-order contributions and effective spin bowling were crucial in setting a competitive total and securing the win.
title: Jeffrey Vandersay grabs six as SL sink India in second ODI
First-class flights: CEO of non-profit outfit slammed for extravagant spending

description: Lakshya Sen will strive to become the first Indian male shuttler to win an Olympic medal as he faces Malaysia's Zii Jia Lee in the bronze medal match at the Paris Games. Meanwhile, Nisha Dahiya will start India's wrestling campaign in the women’s 68kg freestyle pre-quarters.
title: Paris Olympics Day 10: India's Full Schedule

description: The BJP accused the TMC of attempting to manipulate the issue for political gain. According to the BJP, the suspension of MGNREGA funds, which began on March 9, 2022, is not politically motivated but is a response to financial irregularities uncovered during audits by the central government. O’Brien's claimed the Modi government has admitted in Parliament that West Bengal received "zero" funds under MGNREGA.
title: 'Have proof ... habitual duplicity': TMC, BJP lock horns over MGNERGA funding

description: Bangladesh witnessed a resurgence of anti-government protests as demonstrators, demanding Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina's resignation, clashed with government supporters. The unrest stemmed from a controversial job quota system. Police used tear gas and stun grenades to disperse the crowds, and an indefinite nationwide curfew was imposed. PM Hasina labelled the protesters as 'terrorists' and called for their suppression.
title: What is behind violent protests that have erupted in Bangladesh?

description: President Droupadi Murmu departed on a historic six-day visit to Fiji, New Zealand, and Timor-Leste. She engaged in bilateral talks with leaders from all three countries, addressed the Fijian Parliament, and met with the Indian diaspora. The trip highlighted India's Act East Policy, emphasizing the importance of relations with these nations.
title: Watch: Prez Murmu leaves for 6-day visit to Fiji, NZ & Timor-Leste

description: Vice President Kamala Harris will interview three candidates Minnesota Governor Tim Walz, US Senator Mark Kelly, and Pennsylvania Governor Josh Shapiro for her running mate position on Sunday. She plans to announce her choice by Monday, with a public reveal on Tuesday. The decision will impact her campaign and the Democratic Party’s future.
title: Walz, Kelly or Shapiro? Kamala Harris to decide on running mate soon

description: Rangers at Glacier National Park recovered the body of Siddhant Vitthal Patil, a 26-year-old tech professional from India, who drowned in Avalanche Creek on July 6. Patil, who was living in California, fell into the creek while hiking. The search was hampered by obstacles and water conditions. Park officials extended condolences as efforts to repatriate the remains to India begin.
title: Body of Indian techie recovered from US national park after weeks of search

description: Ten days into the Paris Olympics, Manu Bhaker has emerged as one of India's three Olympic medallists in the French capital. The pistol shooter has evolved from being a prominent figure in Indian shooting to becoming a source of inspiration for her fellow countrymen.
title: I don't believe I am a role model yet: Manu Bhaker

description: Intel Corporation witnessed its sharpest single-day stock drop since 1974, losing over $30 billion in market value. The company halted its dividend and announced a 15% workforce reduction amid competition from rivals like TSMC. Intel aims to gather $40 billion through cost cuts and subsidies, though analysts predict a lengthy recovery period.
title: 'Biggest-drop in 50 yrs': Intel loses $30 billion-plus in market value in 1 day

description: Hardeep Puri, minister for petroleum and natural gas, announced the expansion of Assam's Numaligarh Refinery from 3 MMTPA to 9 MMTPA, with completion expected by 2024. A 1,640 km pipeline from Paradip Port to Numaligarh is also under construction for transporting imported crude. The project, costing Rs 28,026 crore, was environmentally cleared in July 2020.
title: Assam refinery capacity to be hiked 3-fold: Petroleum minister Hardeep Puri

description: Union Home Minister Amit Shah called the three new criminal laws the biggest reform of the 21st century. These laws, aimed at ensuring justice for people, will modernize India's criminal justice system. Chandigarh will be the first to fully implement them, promising enhancements like electronic FIR registration and stricter provisions for fleeing criminals.
title: 'Biggest reforms of 21st century': Amit Shah on new criminal laws

description: Hundreds of Silicon Valley tech leaders expressed support for Kamala Harris in a unified statement. They emphasized their belief in democracy and trustworthy institutions. The endorsement aims to counter Trump supporters like Elon Musk and Peter Thiel, who have criticized her policies as harmful to the tech sector.
title: Silicon Valley rallies behind Kamala Harris after Trump makes inroads with Elon Musk

description: Trinamool Congress sought the resignation of West Bengal's correctional homes minister Akhil Giri after a video surfaced showing him verbally abusing a female forest officer. Giri used derogatory language towards Manisha Shaw, calling her disrespectful and threatening her with violence. He later expressed regret and stated he would resign and personally submit it to Chief Minister Mamata Banerjee.
title: 'Apologise, resign': TMC takes action against WB minister for misbehaving with woman official
New law in Assam soon for life imprisonment in 'love jihad' cases: Himanta Sarma

description: When discussing the Indian men's hockey team's victory, it's essential to mention PR Sreejesh, the man who always stands like a rock at the goalpost, consistently denying the opposition's attempts to score.
title: Sreejesh's jaw-dropping save and priceless celebration

description: A teaser of Prince Harry and Meghan Markle's CBS interview drew attention for Harry’s seemingly bored demeanor. Body language expert Judi James highlighted Harry's disengagement compared to Meghan's animated interaction. Addressing their children, Meghan showed affection, while Harry appeared unengaged throughout the clip, leading to speculations about his interest in the interview.
title: Prince Harry appears 'bored' in new interview clip: Experts

description: Playing his last international tournament, goalkeeper PR Sreejesh stood rock solid at the post, making saves after saves in the shoot-out, steering India into the semis. India will play the winner of the quarterfinal match between Germany and Spain in the semis.
title: Watch: Sreejesh points out at wife's name on hockey stick
Worst riots in 13 yrs: Over 100 held in UK as far-right demonstrators clash with counter-protesters
Politicising Ayodhya rape case 'ill-intentioned', says Akhilesh; BJP hits back

description: Protests in Bangladesh on Sunday resulted in the deaths of at least 91 people and numerous injuries as police used tear gas and stun grenades to disperse crowds. Protestors demanded Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina's resignation and called for non-cooperation. The government imposed an indefinite nationwide curfew and shut down high-speed internet services to curb the unrest.
title: B'desh unrest: Toll rises to 91 amid fresh clashes, protesters seek PM's resignation

description: India advanced to the semifinals of the men's hockey event at the Paris Olympics, defeating Great Britain 4-2 in a dramatic penalty shoot-out. Despite playing with 10 men for over 40 minutes after Amit Rohidas's red card, the team's resilience, especially goalkeeper PR Sreejesh's performance, was instrumental in securing this victory.
title: Paris 2024: India enter hockey semis with a thrilling penalty shoot-out win over Great Britain
Looking forward to welcoming first Isro astronaut to ISS: Nasa chief

description: The Delhi-Saharanpur MEMU train derailed during a shunting operation at Saharanpur station yard around 1:30 PM. Fortunately, there were no casualties as the train was empty. The Senior Divisional Commercial Manager’s office confirmed the incident and mentioned that efforts are in place to clear the yard and restore operations. The train had arrived at Saharanpur Junction at 12:26 PM, delayed by over an hour and a half. Railway staff are working to reposition the two derailed coaches. This derailment marks the 10th such incident in the country within the last 18 days.
title: 2 coaches of Delhi-Saharanpur passenger derail in Uttar Pradesh
Violent protests in UK: Over 90 arrested as far-right demonstrations turn into riots

description: The Tibetan Centre for Human Rights and Democracy criticized Douyin, a Chinese social media platform, for banning Tibetan language content. This has affected Tibetan users' ability to create content and earn a living. TCHRD's Tenzin Dawa pointed out that the Chinese constitution permits minority groups to use their language, questioning the restrictions imposed on Tibetan language content.
title: Outrage over Chinese social media platform banning Tibetan language

description: The Indian Computer Emergency Response Team (CERT-In) issued a severe warning to Apple users about vulnerabilities in older versions of iOS, iPadOS, macOS, watchOS, tvOS, visionOS, and Safari.
title: Govt issues 'severe' warning for Apple users, here's what advisory says
'Stop bullshitting me': Biden rebukes Netanyahu in tense call over Gaza ceasefire
Kamala Harris prepares for high-stakes VP selection: Who are top candidates
Former PM Deve Gowda travels in metro during his Delhi visit

description: In Sagar district of Madhya Pradesh, a tragic incident occurred when a 50-year-old mud wall collapsed, killing eight children aged 10 to 14 years and injuring four others. The accident happened near the Hardaul Temple during activities for the month of Sawan, where children were making earthen Shivlings. Rescue efforts were undertaken using JCB machines to clear the debris, and authorities including Rahli MLA and former minister Gopal Bhargava were present at the scene. The collapsed wall was within the temple premises, adding to the mournful event.
title: 9 children dead, 4 injured after wall collapses in Madhya Pradesh

description: Israel sought to create an 'Abraham Alliance' with the US and UK to counter Iranian threats, following coordinated defenses against recent missile and drone attacks. Amid rising tensions, Israeli, American, and British defense leaders called for restraint. President Biden proposed additional US military support for Israel, urging a cease-fire to address the humanitarian crisis in Gaza.
title: 'Abraham Alliance': Israel seeks Nato-like alliance with US, UK to counter Iran threats

description: A 29-year-old woman from Pune fell 50 feet into a gorge at Borne Ghat while taking pictures, after their visit to Thoseghar waterfall was canceled due to heavy rains. Prompt police and volunteer rescue efforts led by Homeguard Abhijeet Mandave helped retrieve her. She was taken to a private hospital for treatment of her injuries.
title: Attempting to click picture, Pune woman falls into gorge
Three bogies of Khoba Express ablaze at Vizag railway station

description: At the Paris Olympics, Indian boxer Nishant Dev lost in the men's 71 kg category to Mexico's Marco Verde, sparking controversy over the fairness of the scoring system. Notable figures, including Vijender Singh and Bollywood actor Randeep Hooda, expressed dissatisfaction with the judges' decisions and the transparency of the scoring system.
title: 'Robbed of medal': Boxer Nishant's loss sparks scoring system debate

description: BJP MP Kangana Ranaut criticized Rahul Gandhi's proposal for a caste census, sharing a morphed picture of the Congress leader. She labeled Gandhi's approach as condescending and questioned his knowledge of his own caste. Social media reactions were mixed, with some supporting Kangana's stance, while others urged her to address issues in her Mandi constituency.
title: Kangana's meme on Rahul over 'caste census' divides social media

description: Recalling the days when he used to open batting for India alongside Rohit Sharma, Shikhar Dhawan shared some interesting little anecdotes to showcase his camaraderie with the India captain in a video on the occasion of 'Friendship Day' being celebrated today (August 4).
title: 'Jab mai ek gana gaata tha...' - Dhawan on friendship with Rohit

description: The Chaliyar River in Kerala, a vital water source for three districts, witnessed tragic landslides in Wayanad on July 30. This natural disaster caused significant loss of life, with 73 bodies and 132 body parts recovered. Rescue operations by multiple agencies, including the Navy and NDRF, are ongoing, raising the death toll to 219.
title: Once a source of life, Chaliyar River now graveyard of Wayanad

description: In Ahmedabad, the population surged from 35 lakh in 1990 to 78 lakh in 2024, yet public transport buses increased marginally from 931 to just over 1,000. Despite the Centre recommending 60 buses per 1 lakh residents, Ahmedabad falls significantly short. The BRTS, launched in 2009, struggles with low ridership as two-wheelers dominate, leading to higher accident fatalities.
title: Only 1,000 buses for 75 lakh people in Ahmedabad

description: Gautam Gambhir's stint as the head coach of the Indian cricket team began positively, with the team, led by newly appointed captain Suryakumar Yadav, achieving a 3-0 clean sweep against Sri Lanka in the three-match T20I series. Gambhir, who has been given a long-term contract until the end of 2027, took over the reins from Rahul Dravid.
title: 'Gambhir jyada lambe samay tak tik nahi payega'

description: The state government managed to send the Nazul Property Bill 2024 to a select committee after protests by legislators. The bill aimed to reclaim encroached nazul land, affecting thousands. Despite clarification that densely occupied land wouldn’t be taken, concerns persisted. The bill seeks to use reclaimed land for public purposes and infrastructure needs.
title: Nazul Property Bill: How an 'anti-land mafia' bill turned into a hot potato
These boys didn't know they were flattening anti-glare screens
Microplastic in West Bengal's Digha and Puri seawater at alarming levels

description: Congress leader Shashi Tharoor faced criticism after describing a visit to landslide-affected Wayanad as 'memorable.' Tharoor defended his language, explaining the term's meaning. The visit featured relief work scenes, drawing backlash from BJP leader Amit Malviya and others who found his description insensitive. The landslides had left significant devastation and loss of life in the region.
title: Did Shashi Tharoor go wrong with words? Flak after 'memorable day' in Wayanad
FIR registered for bomb threat to CM's office in Bihar

description: Several families gathered at AIIMS to honor their loved ones' organ and skin donations, highlighting the selfless act despite challenging rituals and emotional distress. The donations, including those by Raj Dhingra and Rakesh Solanki, demonstrate a growing awareness and contribution towards saving lives amidst low overall donation rates. Experts emphasize the importance of such donations.
title: Families with heart of gold donated organs & skin of loved ones

description: The Income Tax department warned taxpayers about scams involving fake calls and pop-up messages promising tax refunds. These fraudulent calls demand immediate payments, while deceptive texts prompt users to verify bank details. The department clarified it doesn't request payments by phone and urged vigilance, advising to report suspicious activities through official channels.
title: IT return & tax refund: Govt shares screenshots on how criminals are stealing money

description: The Madhya Pradesh forest department considered 'seizing' a train responsible for the death of three tiger cubs on the Midghat-Budhni railway tracks. This follows a precedent set by the Assam government, which seized a locomotive after it killed an elephant and calf in 2020. The incident has deeply affected forest officers, emphasizing the need for strict measures against train overspeeding in tiger corridors.
title: Foresters want to seize train that killed 3 tiger cubs in MP

description: The CEO of Atlys, Mohak Nahta, pledged on LinkedIn to offer free visas to all users for one day if Neeraj Chopra wins a gold medal at the Paris Olympics. Atlys specializes in providing fast travel visas and related services. The post quickly gained traction, sparking excitement and support among fans of Neeraj Chopra.
title: 'Free Visa for everyone' if Neeraj Chopra wins Gold, promises this Indian-origin CEO

description: After being approached by doctors , Sachin's family agreed to donate his organs.
title: Kanwariya who died after being hit by a car gives new life to 5
